Description: Vaultwarden/Bitwarden MCP server for AI agents
 warden-mcp is a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that lets AI agents
 interact with Vaultwarden or Bitwarden password vaults via the official
 Bitwarden CLI (bw). MCP clients can search, create, update, move, and
 read vault items without reimplementing Bitwarden client-side cryptography.
 .
 Supported vault item types include credentials, TOTP codes, secure notes,
 attachments, Sends, folders, organisations, and collections.
 .
 The server operates in HTTP/SSE mode (default, port 3005) for networked
 agents, or in stdio mode for direct integration with desktop MCP hosts
 such as Claude Code or Cursor. The Bitwarden CLI (bw) must be available
 on PATH or its path set via the BW_BIN environment variable.
